title: Properly handle the case where a single IndexedRequest contains multiple delete PlanNode operations on the receiving end of IoTConsensus.
body: A delete operation involving multiple paths or multiple Regions is split into several PlanNodes for execution and synchronization. On the receiving end of IoTConsensus, these PlanNodes need to be merged back into a single PlanNode for execution.

title: Pipe: refactor committer key for event committer after pipe restart to avoid non-monotonic increase
body: During restart, the event committer on each pipe and each region will be destroyed and reinitialized, which resets the commit ID. If an event is sent by the async connector before destruction, the callback for this event may be executed after the committer is initialized, potentially leading to confusion in the commit ID...

title: Fix query stuck caused by restarting DN while doing query
body:
If we restart a DN while doing a query and then fetchStateAndUpdate may throw TException and won't record that FI's state.
If that FI is just rootFI, then if we use the old code:
```
    boolean queryFinished =
        instanceStateMap.values().stream()
            .filter(instanceStateMetrics -> instanceStateMetrics.isRootInstance)
            .allMatch(
                instanceStateMetrics ->
                    instanceStateMetrics.lastState == FragmentInstanceState.FINISHED);
```

It will return true.

title: Pipe: release resources of pipe event that have been GCed but the reference count is not zero by PhantomReference
body: Considering that when the event is garbage collected, the file resources it holds will not automatically end their lifecycle, we adopt a reference counting maintenance + safety net fallback method (releasing resources later is better than never releasing them).

title: Fix WAL Exception catch & support new DataTypes in QueryDataSetUtils
body:
One Tablet deserialization does not support new types in QueryDataSetUtils, which causes WAL recovery failure.
TsDataType switches are supplemented with all cases to indicate they are CONSIDERED rather than FORGOTTEN.
